OL,3,CSussex Wildlife Trust demands action
OL,4,Cafter bio-bead pollution hits 50 mile
OL,5,Ccoast
OL,7,FSussex Wildlife Trust has called on
OL,8,FSouthern Water to stop the use of bio-
OL,9,Fbeads in treatment water, after
OL,10,Fmillions of them were released into
OL,11,Fthe sea.
OL,13,FThe Trust's Chief Executive Chris
OL,14,FCorrigan had a private meeting with
OL,15,Fhis Southern Water counterpart where
OL,16,Fhe asked them why the spill happened,
OL,17,Fwhat the water company intend to do
OL,18,Fabout it and how they intend to
OL,19,Fprevent any future incidents.
